A big "Thank You!" to our partners at Quest for preparing breakfast and lunch for our to-go pick up tomorrow morning! This is the first day meals will be provided to District 146 families for all children in the household under 18 years of age.

Tomorrow, Monday, March 23, Meals will be distributed from 7:15-8:45 a.m. at the following locations:
Central Middle School (Tinley Park), Door #7
Fierke Education Center (Oak Forest), Door #8
Kruse Education Center (Orland Park), Door #8

Families can pick up meals at any location, regardless of which schools their children attend.

Our D146 Buildings and Grounds crews are experiencing some difficulty in keeping up with the grass cutting due to the near record rainfall this month. It has caused extreme saturation of the grounds. If you see that the grass is a bit taller than usual, please be patient as we give the grounds an opportunity to dry out so we can get back to our regular maintenance schedule. Thank you for your understanding.

If you have any concerns, please contact the District office at 708-614-4500. The District truly appreciates the community’s understanding and continued support.

post_text:
Message from Dr. Jeff Stawick, Superintendent:

Police have given Central Middle School the all clear to return to the building. Buses will begin taking Central students back to Central Middle School at 1:15 p.m.

Students of parents who are already in line to pick-up their child at Memorial will remain at Memorial until reunited with their parent.

Regular afternoon bus service home will be available for CMS students as usual.

All after-school and evening events at CMS have been cancelled tonight.

The Tinley Park Police Department and CMS administration have begun a rigorous investigation to identify the identity of the person that made the threat.

Thank you to the administration and staff of CMS and Memorial for their hard work keeping kids safe today and always.

Thank you to Tinley Park Police Department for their expertise and outstanding service.

Thank you to all parents for their patience and understanding.

The Tinley Park Police Department and CMS administration have begun a rigorous investigation to identify the identity of the person that made the threat.

Thank you to the administration and staff of CMS and Memorial for their hard work keeping kids safe today and always.

Thank you to all parents for their patience and understanding.

post_text:
All Central Middle School students have arrived safely at Memorial School. Memorial Welcomed them with open arms and has now provided the following procedures for parents wishing to pick up their child.

Parents can come to the front door at Memorial with an ID and sign their child out, if they desire.

Students who are not picked up will return to Central Middle school when the police give the all clear signal. Thank you to Central Middle School and Memorial faculty and staff for their attention to keeping all students safe.
text:
All Central Middle School students have arrived safely at Memorial School. Memorial Welcomed them with open arms and has now provided the following procedures for parents wishing to pick up their child.

post_text:
This morning, Central Middle School received a bomb threat that we believe is not credible. However, in the interest of safety, CMS students have been moved to Memorial School. As soon as police say CMS is all clear, students will return there.

Please do not go to Memorial at this time. As soon as we have a release procedure in place, parents will be notified that they may pick up their child if they desire. In the meantime, know that your child is safe and there is no danger at Memorial School.

post_text: Way to go, Twisters! Good luck tomorrow!
shared_text:
Central Middle School
October 2, 2018 at 3:23 PM ·

Softball Update:

The girls’ softball team gave the previously undefeated Evergreen their first and only loss of the regular season with a score of 3-2! With a tie going into the bottom of the 7th inning, Melanie A. draws a lead off walk, Megan K. comes up a with a huge double to move the runners to 2nd and 3rd and Megan P. lays down the perfect bunt to win the game with a safety squeeze. The defense that held them to only two runs was led by Cami S. with her amazing pitching. The entire team played fantastic softball. Nice job Ladies. The girls play again on Thursday.
